As much as I'd /LIKE/ to think this will get changed, and somehow my now eternally jaded image of what Verant and EverQuest stand for will be changed -  but it won't.<br>
<br>
Nothing has ever come of any attempt to get something changed. . .  maybe a bone thrown in, but noting real, nothing tangible.  It took them 8 months of people pointing it out to them in plain english why Alchemy was broken.  I remember reading posts of people saying, in easy to read pre-formated letters, "Alchemy is broken, I cannot train it.  I am a Shaman of approriate level.  Please stop using artificially buffed characters and try to TRAIN IT USING A REAL CHARACTER and you will see the problem."  And those were only a month and a half into the ordeal.<br>
<br>
I think in Incar BP was perfect. .  it wasn't broken, it wasn't overpowered, hell . .  it was only USEFUL for a select few people.  High level monks, pallies and clerics who needed it for the invis and warriors without cobalt legs.  Verant has now decided its time to make the high-end game even harder.  Its time to lock people into a routine so ingrained in them they'll never break free from EQ.  Verant has realized opposition for their "King of the Hill" position in the MMOG market is starting to walk up the mount.  And just like with UO, they're gonna lose a huge amount of their player base no matter what they do.  On UO, right before EQ went retail OSI got really nice and lovey . .  hoping to keep players there.  Verant's trying another tactic : "If they don't love us, we'll beat them to the point they have no choice.  We'll squeeze our iron fist so tight the only one's that matter are the few that fall out."<br>
<br>
Well Verant. .   news flash . . .  people aren't stupid.  We've seen what EA.com and eFront have done. . .  we're aware of the schlocky practices that online businesses use.  The problem with "ecommerce" is that there's nothing tangible about it.  I betcha no-one has ever stormed into Verant HQ and demanded a refund to their faces.  They don't have to deal with us if they don't want to -  because they know there're really no alternatives.  Like I said. .  wake up Verant, you're about to be in the same spot OSI was in.  How does it feel to know you're about to become the "old game" that people talk about and "remember the good ol' days".  I remember my good days in EQ, they ended over a year ago -  when it stopped being fun.  As of the end of May. . .  EverQuest is gonna be second rate<br>
<br>
Kithoo -  This is your 8:30 AM wake up call</td></tr></table><br><p>[ No Comments Allowed for Anonymous, please <a href="user.php">register</a>  ]</font><p><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=1419&sid=166&pid=1418&mode=thread&order=0&thold=0#1419">Re: You know why they did this. . .</a> by Anonymous <font size=2>on Wednesday, March 28 @ 12:21:05 EST</font><br><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=1477&sid=166&pid=1418&mode=thread&order=0&thold=0#1477">Here's what I dont understand</a> by Anonymous <font size=2>on Saturday, March 31 @ 12:23:13 EST</font><br><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=1479&sid=166&pid=1477&mode=thread&order=0&thold=0#1479">Re: Here's what I dont understand</a> by Anonymous <font size=2>on Saturday, March 31 @ 17:21:44 EST</font><br></ul></ul></p><a name="1421"></a><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td width=500><p><b>Re: Incardine BP nerf, BAH!</b> <font size=2>(Score: 1)<br>by <a href="mailto:Briae@dragonslore.com">Briae</a> <b>(Briae@dragonslore.com)</b> on Wednesday, March 28 @ 13:19:22 EST<br>(<a href="user.php?op=userinfo&uname=Briae">User Info</a>) </font></td></tr><tr><td>Kithoo, you have hit the nail right on the fucking head!!<br>
