<br>
"For nearly a year, the incarnadine BP has been an SK/WAR item that was useable by anybody from an inventory slot to grant gather shadows (self-only invis) This last patch the BP was nerfed so that now it must be worn for the effect to be used.<br>
<br>
In a lot of cases this item has been going to clerics, paladins, and monks simply for the effect as on a good portion of Chardok royalty raids the present SKs and warriors already have a better breastplate. Basically this nerf hurts the people who won or were given the BP on one of these raids such as myself.<br>
<br>
The first question I have is why is this item unbalanced? There are a lot of ways for anybody to cast invis. Potions cost 15 plat each...you can get a 5 charge invis item from your local tinker and recharge it using mana batteries. You can get a 10 charge camo mask from Seblis. Basically this was a convenience item...a way that a few very high level individuals on each server could be rewarded by having an inexhaustible self-invis item which took only one inventory slot instead of a full bag. I could also ask the question of why warriors (the biggest, least stealthiest class in the game) get an invisible effect but other classes don't, but I'll leave that out since this isn't a class balance thread.<br>
<br>
The most common response I have heard about this nerf is the following: "it says WAR/SK on it....anybody else using it was exploiting a bug. This item wasn't nerfed, it was fixed." My response: a lot of items that are usable by only certain classes may be used by anybody from inventory slots. For example, the amulet of necropotence is a caster only wearable neck that anybody can use for illusion: skeleton. Lots of large races use it to make themselves smaller. You all know this item may be used in this manner...in the first test of tactics entire teams used it to turn themselves into all skeletons right in front of many dev team members and GMs. Another example is the staff of forbidden rights. This is a priest only equippable item that has the effect of the level 49 cleric ressurection spell but anybody can use this item from inventory. Why is it ok for an SK to use a priest item to cast ressurection but not ok for a cleric to use an SK item to cast gather shadows? There are several more of these items but I think my point has been made...if no items were supposed to be used by classes who could not equip them, then why are there so many of them...and why just pick and choose one of them seemingly at random to change?<br>
<br>
I also happen to have a guise of the deceiver...it's a rogue/bard mask that casts illusion: dark elf; anybody can use from inventory. This item was changed a long time ago. All of the existing ones were left as is...but a new item began dropping that was nearly identical but had to be worn for the effect to be used. This was a good change. Nobody wanted to see an entire world full of nothing but dark elves (well, maybe a few people did) but the people who had already earned the item were allowed to keep it. I know this was done because many more people had a guise of the deceiver than have an incarnadine BP...but by the same token that means that the breastplate if far more meaningful to the few who have them. It was also a rare drop off a mob you need a full raid to kill, unlike the guise you can solo to get.<br>
<br>
I guess my point is that if you have an item in the game this long it should not retroactively changed. Go the way of the guise and make new ones which have to be worn if you must. I could understand if it was an unbalancing item but it is not...out of flavor maybe but not unbalancing. The high level mobs in EQ take a lot of people to kill and only drop a few items each. This means that when you win or are rewarded with an item, depending on how your raid or guild does it, you probably aren't going to get another high end item for a while. This item has been going to monks, paladins, and clerics now for a long long time...it stinks to have it made completely worthless now and I would appreciate a response.<br>
<br>
P.S. Sorry to everybody if I get the staff of forbidden rights, amulet of necropotence, and any other items retroactively nerfed."<br>
<br>
Delnatha Powa<br>
Grandmaster of Afterlife<br>
ToT2 Champion</td></tr></table><br><p>[ No Comments Allowed for Anonymous, please <a href="user.php">register</a>  ]</font><p></ul></p></td><td bgcolor=ffffff><img src=themes/NukeNews/pixel.gif width=10 height=1 border=0></td></tr></table>

